<br>
Communicate and try every means possible to resolve the situation IN GAME. If you talk to the person directly and log the convesation, then you may find some evidence there. A person that cusses and is rude and admits that they did something will definitely be easier to judge. Talk to their guild. If this person has a history of this behavior, they may get kicked out of the guild. If they do not have an adequate explaination, then they may get kicked out of the guild. If a player's support base can't even support their actions anymore, then this also gives me some knowledge about the person and their actions. Talk to the GMs. If the person gets banned for a week, then yeah, I'm ready to believe your side of the story. If they don't get banned, then your story still has some weight, but there was something in the offense that was missing so that a warning or a banning could not take place. Again, this is useful information.<br>
<br>
If its a group situation, you may want your group members to post on the SL and verify your story. This also supports your statements. <br>
<br>
Finally, if you are gonna try to SL someone for being rude, you better log the conversation. I'm sorry, but some people think using the word &quot;God&quot; is inappropriate. I'm not gonna destroy someone elses reputation for excessive use of this word. I can't just take your word that someone was &quot;Rude&quot; to you because its very subjective. Show me logs and let me make my own descision.<br>
<br>
Remember that the SL represents the possible destruction of someone elses reputation. The fun that you so cherish in the game, may, in many instances, be taken away from this person. Its a pretty severe thing to do and it requires proof from many sources. In the end, people will make their own decisions to aviod the person or not, but to make those decisions, YOU (the Poster), must provide adequate EVIDENCE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uihaveasukhandle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ihaveasukhandle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/31/01 7:39:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Following the Rules of the SL</span><hr size=1> Being this is a rant and raves area. <br>
